<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lordly" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lordly,</orth> high, proud; in a good as well as in a bad sense: <cit><quote>his l. crew,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1731" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1731</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>ay, l. sir,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 43</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a l. nation,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 62</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the l. monarch of the north,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>her l. peers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>your l. lord-protectorship,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 30</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the George hath lost his l. honour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.369" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 369</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>holy</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>